        <br>
      
        <p>A hot dog is a type of sausage that is typically made from a blend of ground meat, such as beef or pork, along with various spices and seasonings. The sausage is often shaped like a long, thin tube, and is typically served in a soft,white bun with various condiments, such as ketchup, mustard, onions, and relish.</p>
        <p><center></center></p>
    <header>
        
            <div class="header-line"></div>
          </header> 
          <div class="wrapper">
		<div class="left-box">
			<h2>ingredients</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Ground meat: Most commonly beef or pork, but sometimes a combination of the two.</li>
				<li>Salt: To add flavor and act as a preservative.</li>
				<li>Water: To help bind the ingredients together and create a moist texture.</li>
        <li>Spices: Such as paprika, garlic, and onion powder, to add flavor.</li>
        <li>Preservatives: Such as sodium nitrate or sodium erythorbate, to help extend the shelf life of the hot dog.</li>
        <li>Other ingredients may include corn syrup, dextrose, or other sweeteners, to balance out the saltiness of the meat.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<div class="right-box">
			<h1>Method</h1>
			<ol>
        <li>Preheat a grill, grill pan, or skillet over medium-high heat.</li>
        <li>Place the hotdog sausages on the grill or in the pan and cook for 3-5 minutes on each side, until browned and heated through.</li>
        <li>While the hotdogs are cooking, warm the hotdog buns by placing them on the grill or in the oven for a few minutes.</li>
        <li>Once the hotdogs are cooked, remove them from the heat and place them in the warmed buns.</li>
        <li>Add your desired condiments and toppings to the hotdogs.</li>
        <li>Serve immediately and enjoy!</li>
      </ol>
	</div>
